ical introduction that conveys the powerful story of the sisters' survival from capture to freedom in 1946.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)vPoetry. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)xPoetry. 7aPOETRY / Anthologies (multiple authors).2bisacsh1 aKarmel, Ilona, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520940741423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520940741.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles